  "_doc": "Phase-7 demo: small mixed circuit that exercises the full Export UX. Click VERILOG to see:\n  • Syntax highlight + line numbers + stats bar (lines / ports / nets / assigns / always / mem).\n  • Header toggle on the right — flip on to add the file header.\n  • TOP-name text field — rename the module live; filename + DOWNLOAD .v update with it.\n  • TESTBENCH button — emits a self-contained `_tb.v` that drives the clock, zeroes inputs, dumps a VCD, ready for `iverilog -g2005 design.v design_tb.v && vvp ./a.out`.\n  • PROJECT .ZIP button — bundles design + testbench + a README into one archive.\n  • Stage comment dividers — the COUNTER and stage_reg carry `stage` attributes, so the body shows `// ─── Stage 0 ───` / `// ─── Stage 1 ───` separators.\n  • Right-click any block on canvas → `Copy as Verilog` to grab a single-component snippet to the clipboard.",
